      "span_text": "It is possible that interventions that aim explicitly to increase people's opportunities (and so capacity for self-determination), skills (and so capacity for self-governance) and self-evaluative attitudes (and so capacity for self-authorisation) also enable people to engage in more autonomous health promoting actions, however the value of fostering of autonomy is not contingent on any associated health improvement."
